Reasoning: The paper deals with a counterexample to a lemma used in a recent tentative improvement of the Pin-Frankl bound for synchronizing automata. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof techniques, which could place it under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which could place it under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
